sentences: She was born in Havana, Cuba, and has lived in Miami, Florida, since 1988.
In 1988, her family moved to Miami, where she still lives.

In 1993, an audition got her a scholarship to enter the University of Miami School of Music to study Jazz Vocal Performance, thanks to an audition, she was chosen by record producers to sing on various projects for major labels.
In 2002, Yisel started a jazz group named "Common Time", with a fusion of influences and different styles.
In September 2014, she pre-released her debut album Life Is ... , with a sold-out concert in the Jackie Gleason Theater of Miami Beach.
